 projects employees have opportunities all year long to volunteer with our arts culture and youth nonprofit partners volunteer grants turner gives monetary donations to a nonprofit or school with which an employee regularly volunteers volunteer release time employees can receive up to  hours of volunteer release time annually to support volunteerism during the workweek contributions  grants turner voices turner’s signature corporate philanthropy program strategically invests in community arts and culture and youth development our support leverages our people products technology and services to identify and develop a pipeline of future storytellers and talent walks  runs turner funds local walkrun employee teams in support of nonprofit causes matching grants turner matches a portion of an employee donation made to nonprofit organizations environmental concerns resource conservation turner makes constant efforts to conserve energy and water and reduce waste on a large scale through constant facilities improvements and employee recycling programs green commuting turner’s clean air commuter program encourages employees to help reduce pollution and highway congestion by using mass transit carpools and vanpools electric car charging stations are available to employees at several work locations employees can purchase transit passes and parking vouchers or elect parking reimbursement with funds deducted from paychecks on a pretax basis through the transportation services program program offerings differ by location turner broadcasting system  wikipedia turner broadcasting system from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search this article is about the company for the channel owned by this company see tbs us tv channel this article needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed february  learn how and when to remove this template message turner broadcasting system inc the cnn center which houses the headquarters of turner broadcasting system type division industry entertainment cable television mass media interactive media predecessor turner communications group founded   years ago  founder ted turner headquarters cnn center atlanta georgia us key people john k martin ceo  chairman david levy president products cnn cnn international hln tnt turner classic movies cartoon network boomerang adult swim trutv tbs cnn airport parent time warner sale to att pending divisions turner sports subsidiaries turner broadcasting system europe turner broadcasting system asia pacific turner broadcasting system latin america cartoon network studios studio t turner private networks hulu  williams street istreamplanet majority stake lts garðbær studios website wwwturnercom turner broadcasting system inc known professionally as turner broadcasting system and also known simply as turner is an american media conglomerate that is a division of time warner and manages the collection of cable television networks and properties initiated or acquired by ted turner the company was founded in  and merged with time warner on october   it now operates as a semiautonomous unit of time warner the companys assets include cnn hln tbs tnt cartoon network adult swim boomerang and trutv the companys current chairman and ceo is john k martin the headquarters of turners properties are located in both the cnn center in downtown atlanta and the turner broadcasting campus off techwood drive in midtown atlanta which also houses turner studios across interstate  from the techwood campus is the original home of turners wtbs superstation now separated into its tbs cable network and peachtree tv which today houses the headquarters of adult swim and williams street productions contents  history  s  s  s  s  s  properties  us domestic  international  other regions  former assets  references  external links historyedit sedit in  ted turner then owner of a successful atlantabased outdoor advertising company purchased wjrjatlanta channel  a small struggling ultra high frequency station and renamed it wtcg for parent company turner communications group by careful programming acquisitions turner guided the station to success during december  wtcg originated the superstation concept transmitting via satellite to cable systems on december   at  pm wtcg channel s signal was beamed via satellite to its four cable systems in grand island nebraska newport news virginia troy alabama and newton kansas all four cable systems started receiving the  dana andrews  cesar romero film deep waters already in progress the movie had started  minutes earlier wtcg went from being a little television station to a major tv network that every one of the  households outside of the  in atlanta was receiving coasttocoast wtcg became a socalled superstation and created a precedent of todays basic cable television hbo had gone to satellite transmissions to distribute its signal nationally in  but that was a service cable subscribers were made to pay extra to receive ted turners innovation signaled the start of the basic cable revolution in  the company changed its name to turner broadcasting system inc tbs inc and the call letters of its main entertainment channel to wtbs sedit on june   cnn was launched at  est becoming the first hour news cable channel the husband and wife team of dave walker and lois hart news anchored the first newscast burt reinhardt the then executive vice president of cnn hired most of cnns first  employees  member staff including bernard shaw the networks first news anchor in  turner broadcasting system acquired brut productions from faberge inc in  turner initiated cable music channel his competition for wasecs mtv the channel was shortlived but helped influence the original format of vh in  after a failed attempt to acquire cbs turner purchased the film studio mgmua entertainment co from kirk kerkorian for  billion following the acquisition turner had an enormous debt and sold parts of the acquisition mgmua entertainment was sold back to kirk kerkorian the mgmua studio lot in culver city was sold to lorimartelepictures turner kept mgms premay  film and tv library as well as the associated artists productions library the pre warner bros film library and the fleischer studiosfamous studios popeye cartoons originally released by paramount pictures the uscanadian distribution rights to the rko pictures library and gilligans island and its animated spinoffs turner entertainment co was founded on august   on october   the company launched turner network television tnt sedit turner expanded its presence in movie production and distribution first with the  purchase of the hannabarbera animation studio on december   turner acquired castle rock entertainment turner purchased new line cinema a month later turner launched cartoon network on october   followed by turner classic movies tcm on april   on october   turner merged with time warner a company formed in  by the merger of time inc and warner communications through this merger warner bros had regained the rights to its pre library while turner gained access to the companys post library and other properties sedit in  philip i kent succeeded jamie kellner as chairman operational duties for the wb were transferred by time warner from warner bros to turner broadcasting during  while kellner was chairman but were returned to warner bros in  with the departure of kellner on february   the company agreed to sell the regional entertainment channel turner south to fox entertainment group fox assumed control of the channel on may  and on october  relaunched it as sportsouth  coincidentally the former name of fox sports south when turner owned this channel in partnership with liberty media between  and  in may  time warner which had owned  of court tv since  purchased the remaining  from liberty media and began running the channel as part of turner broadcasting the channel was relaunched as trutv on january   also in may  ted turner attended his last meeting as a board member of time warner and officially parted with the company on october   turner broadcasting system completed the acquisition of claxson interactive pay television networks in latin americaunreliable source sedit on august   turner broadcasting took full control of chilevisión a tv channel owned by chiles president sebastián piñera on september   turner broadcasting system acquired lazytown entertainment the producer of the tv series lazytown on january   john k martin succeeded phil kent as chairman and ceo of turner broadcasting in august  the wrap reported that turner was preparing to offer buyouts to  employees as part of plans to restructure the company heading into  the ratings performance of cnn and hln were cited as a factor while cbssportscom reported that the rising rights fees turner pays for its nba broadcasts on tnt may have also been a factor it was further reported in october  that the company planned to reduce its workforce by   people through layoffs across a wide set of units including corporate positions on august   it was announced that turner broadcasting had acquired a majority stake in istreamplanet a las vegasbased video streaming services company in an effort to bolster its overthetop programming and shift its core technology infrastructure to the cloud istreamplanet is a direct competitor of major league baseball advanced media the deal was reported to be in the neighborhood of  million in april  in order to expedite the sale of time warner to att by shedding fcclicensed properties wpchtv was sold to meredith corporation it had already been operating wpch on its behalf since  as a sister to its local station wgcltv former turner broadcasting system logo used from  to november   propertiesedit this section has multiple issues please help improve it or discuss these issues on the talk page learn how and when to remove t