 animation studio sportsouth — a regional sports network now owned by st century fox as fox sports south new line cinema — a film production company new line television — a television production arm of new line productions turner publishing — a book publisher turner entertainment co — a film holding company turner pictures — an original inhouse programming turner pictures worldwide distribution — an international distribution sales unit turner feature animation — an animation unit turner home entertainment — a home video distributor merged into warner home video turner program services — a former syndication arm − merged into warner bros telepictures productions turner south — a regional television channel now owned by fox sports networks as fox sports southeast universal wrestling corporation  a professional wrestling promotion formerly known as world championship wrestling currently a nonoperational company select assets are now owned by wwe inc through wcw inc wpchtv  a terrestrial broadcasting station and a former superstation now owned by meredith corporation  now owned or absorbed by sister company warner bros referencesedit  httprevenuesandprofitscomhowtimewarnermakesmoney  pressroom turner   andreeva nellie august   david levy upped to president of turner broadcasting system deadline hollywood retrieved june     yu roger october   att agrees to buy time warner for  billion usa today retrieved june     john martin bio turner   contact us turner broadcasting system  terms of use retrieved  june    faberge sells bruts assets httpwwwnytimescom new york times retrieved  november   external link in website help  you must remember this the warner bros story  p   media history digital library   new tnt channel begins monday on cable systems the buffalo news  october    lippman john october   turner is buying hannabarbera film library los angeles times retrieved september     harris kathryn august   new line cinema holding merger talks with turner   citron alan augus